content:
Creating an HTML webpage that provides tips for enhancing listening abilities is a great idea. Below is a simple HTML code that includes the techniques you mentioned: active listening, comprehensive questioning, empathy, paying attention to non-verbal cues, and verifying comprehension. It also includes a basic formula for assessing the effectiveness of one's listening skills.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Enhance Your Listening Abilities</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
        }
        header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        section {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #333;
        }
        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
        }
        .formula {
            background-color: #e2eafc;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Tips for Enhancing Your Listening Abilities</h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Techniques to Enhance Listening Skills</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Active Listening:</strong> Engage fully with the speaker, showing that you are paying attention through nodding, verbal affirmations, and eye contact.</li>

            <li><strong>Comprehensive Questioning:</strong> Ask questions that help clarify the speaker's message and demonstrate your understanding.</li>

            <li><strong>Empathy:</strong> Try to understand the speaker's feelings and perspective, showing compassion and sensitivity to their viewpoint.</li>

            <li><strong>Paying Attention to Non-Verbal Cues:</strong> Observe body language, facial expressions, and tone of voice to gain a deeper understanding of the message.</li>

            <li><strong>Verifying Comprehension:</strong> Summarize or paraphrase what has been said to ensure you have understood the message correctly.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Assessing Your Listening Skills</h2>
        <p>To assess the effectiveness of your listening skills, you can use the following formula:</p>
        <div class="formula">
            <p><strong>Listening Effectiveness = (Understanding + Retention + Response) / 3</strong></p>
        </div>
        <p>Where:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Understanding:</strong> How well you comprehend the information.</li>
            <li><strong>Retention:</strong> How well you remember the information.</li>
            <li><strong>Response:</strong> How appropriately you respond to the information.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

</body>
</html>
```

This code creates a simple and clean webpage that outlines techniques to improve listening skills and provides a method to assess listening effectiveness. You can further enhance the design and content as needed.
